= Experiences

== Education

=== PhD (博士課程), Applied Informatics --- Hosei University, Tokyo
/2025 -- 2028 (expected)/

Graduate School of Science and Engineering (Applied Informatics), [https://iist.hosei.ac.jp/2025/10/20/associate-professor-keping-yu-recognized-as-one-of-the-worlds-top-2-scientists-by-stanford-university-and-elsevier-2025-edition/ *YuLab*], [https://iist.hosei.ac.jp IIST Koganei Campus]. Doctoral research on *AI / sLM / LLM* methods for smart-grid stability, multi-impairment analysis, and SCADA anomaly detection on *IoT-instrumented* power systems. All training and inference run on dedicated multi-GPU servers I configure, maintain, and scale. Advisor: [https://iist.hosei.ac.jp/2025/10/20/associate-professor-keping-yu-recognized-as-one-of-the-worlds-top-2-scientists-by-stanford-university-and-elsevier-2025-edition/ Prof. Keping Yu] (recognised among Stanford / Elsevier *World's Top 2% Scientists*, 2025 edition).

=== MSc, Applied Informatics --- Hosei University, Tokyo
/2023 -- 2025/

Master's research on transformer-based forecasting for IoT energy systems (TAPformer, TSFormer, CNN-BiLSTM hybrid). VTC2024-Fall paper awarded the IEEE VTS Tokyo/Japan Chapter Student Paper Award.

== Research experience

=== Doctoral researcher --- YuLab, Hosei University
/2025 -- present, Tokyo/

First-authored *2 Q1 journal papers* and *5 IEEE flagship conference papers* on *IoT* energy systems and *sLM*-based forecasting / anomaly detection. Building a unified co-optimization framework for smart-grid stability with formal bounds and *sLM*-based SCADA anomaly prediction, all running on a dedicated multi-GPU server in the YuLab.
~~~
{}{raw}
<details class="more"><summary>What I do day to day</summary>
<div class="more-body">
<ul>
  <li>Design dual-domain graph-neural-network architectures for power-system stability at scale (up to 2,869 buses, PEGASE benchmark).</li>
  <li>Develop the spectral-to-language reprogramming pipeline (Spec2Llama, Spec2LLM, LLM4Imp) targeting both LLM and <strong>small-language-model (sLM)</strong> backbones for <strong>IoT</strong>-edge-friendly deployment.</li>
  <li>Provision and operate a <strong>dedicated multi-GPU server</strong> for the lab: CUDA / PyTorch environment, distributed training jobs, model checkpointing, inference services.</li>
  <li>Lead international collaborations with King Saud University (Profs. Tolba, Alfarraj), Mohamed Bin Zayed University of AI (Prof. Guizani), University of British Columbia (Prof. Leung).</li>
  <li>Mentor incoming Master's students in the YuLab on transformer architectures, spectral methods, and GPU-cluster workflows.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
~~~

=== Master's researcher --- YuLab, Hosei University
/2023 -- 2025, Tokyo/

Foundational work on attention-based transformers for *IoT* load forecasting and edge intelligence. Set up the lab GPU-server training pipeline that the doctoral work now extends. The Master's-period VTC2024-Fall paper won the *IEEE VTS Tokyo/Japan Chapter 2024 Student Paper Award*.
~~~
{}{raw}
<details class="more"><summary>What I built during the Master's</summary>
<div class="more-body">
<ul>
  <li>TAPformer (long-term IoT load forecasting), TSFormer (multi-horizon transformer), and the hybrid attention-based CNN-BiLSTM that won the VTS award.</li>
  <li>Spectral-aware forecasting line of work begun, later evolving into Spec2Llama / Spec2LLM / LLM4Imp during the doctoral course.</li>
  <li>First-author oral presentations at IEEE VTC2024-Fall and ICUFN 2025.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</details>
~~~

== Industry experience

=== Full-stack Developer & AI --- *D'isum Inc.*
/Sep 2024 -- Jun 2025, Tokyo · Part-time/

- *Sensor Data Pipeline Architect & Analyst* --- building pipelines from raw sensor data.
- *Sensor Data Specialist* --- app development, prototyping and integration; full scope covering development, architecture / prototypes, and team collaboration on core software integration.
- *Precision Sensor Data Engineer --- Analytics, ML Prototypes & System Fusion* --- incorporating ML / predictive elements, prototyping, and integrating new systems with existing ones.

=== Internship --- *[https://www.jica.go.jp/english/index.html JICA (Japan International Cooperation Agency)]*
/July 2024, Tokyo --- 1 month/

Hands-on introduction to *Generative AI applied to real-world business problems*: discovery, prototyping, and demonstrating LLM-powered solutions for the consulting practice. First substantial exposure to building production GenAI systems for industry clients.

=== TICAD9 booth --- *[https://www.jica.go.jp/english/index.html JICA]* representative
/August 2025, Yokohama/

Returned to support JICA at the *9th Tokyo International Conference on African Development ([https://www.jica.go.jp/english/our_work/types_of_assistance/ticad/index.html TICAD9])*. Staffed the JICA booth and demonstrated applied ML and GenAI prototypes for African energy and infrastructure use cases to a high-traffic, international audience including African delegations.

